		private const string OpeningThisWeekResponce = "{\"movies\":[{\"id\":\"771355832\",\"title\":\"The Other Woman\",\"year\":2014,\"mpaa_rating\":\"PG-13\",\"runtime\":109,\"critics_consensus\":\"The Other Woman definitely boasts a talented pedigree, but all that skill is never fully brought to bear on a story that settles for cheap laughs instead of reaching its empowering potential.\",\"release_dates\":{\"theater\":\"2014-04-25\"},\"ratings\":{\"critics_rating\":\"Rotten\",\"critics_score\":25,\"audience_rating\":\"Upright\",\"audience_score\":70},\"synopsis\":\"After discovering her boyfriend is married, a woman (Cameron Diaz) tries to get her ruined life back on track. But when she accidentally meets the wife he's been cheating on (Leslie Mann), she realizes they have much in common, and her sworn enemy becomes her greatest friend. When yet another affair is discovered (Kate Upton), all three women team up to plot mutual revenge on their cheating, lying, three-timing SOB. (c) Sony\",\"posters\":{\"thumbnail\":\"http://content8.flixster.com/movie/11/17/76/11177622_mob.jpg\",\"profile\":\"http://content8.flixster.com/movie/11/17/76/11177622_pro.jpg\",\"detailed\":\"http://content8.flixster.com/movie/11/17/76/11177622_det.jpg\",\"original\":\"http://content8.flixster.com/movie/11/17/76/11177622_ori.jpg\"},\"abridged_cast\":[{\"name\":\"Cameron Diaz\",\"id\":\"162654443\",\"characters\":[\"Carly\"]},{\"name\":\"Leslie Mann\",\"id\":\"162664741\",\"characters\":[\"Kate\"]},{\"name\":\"Kate Upton\",\"id\":\"771388062\",\"characters\":[\"Amber\"]},{\"name\":\"Nikolaj Coster-Waldau\",\"id\":\"559808757\",\"characters\":[\"Mark\"]},{\"name\":\"Nicki Minaj\",\"id\":\"771446126\",\"characters\":[\"Lydia\"]}],\"alternate_ids\":{\"imdb\":\"2203939\"},\"links\":{\"self\":\"http://api.rottentomatoes.com/api/public/v1.0/movies/771355832.json\",\"alternate\":\"http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_other_woman_2014/\",\"cast\":\"http://api.rottentomatoes.com/api/public/v1.0/movies/771355832/cast.json\",\"clips\":\"http://api.rottentomatoes.com/api/public/v1.0/movies/771355832/clips.json\",\"reviews\":\"http://api.rottentomatoes.com/api/public/v1.0/movies/771355832/reviews.json\",\"similar\":\"http://api.rottentomatoes.com/api/public/v1.0/movies/771355832/similar.json\"}},{\"id\":\"771372645\",\"title\":\"Brick Mansions\",\"year\":2014,\"mpaa_rating\":\"PG-13\",\"runtime\":90,\"critics_consensus\":\"Choppily edited and largely bereft of plot, Brick Mansions wastes a likable cast on a pointless remake of the far more entertaining District B13.\",\"release_dates\":{\"theater\":\"2014-04-25\"},\"ratings\":{\"critics_rating\":\"Rotten\",\"critics_score\":29,\"audience_rating\":\"Spilled\",\"audience_score\":58},\"synopsis\":\"In a dystopian Detroit, abandoned brick mansions left from better times now house only the most dangerous criminals. Unable to control the crime, the police constructed a colossal containment wall around this area to protect the rest of the city. For undercover cop Damien Collier (Paul Walker) every day is a battle against corruption. For Lino (David Belle), every day is a fight to live an honest life. Their paths never should have crossed, but when drug kingpin, Tremaine (RZA) kidnaps Lino's girlfriend, Damien reluctantly accepts the help of the fearless ex-convict, and together they must stop a sinister plot to devastate the entire city. With stylized action featuring thrilling Parkour stunts (David Belle is the co-founder of this physical training discipline), Brick Mansions puts an entertaining twist on the action genre. (c) Relativity\",\"posters\":{\"thumbnail\":\"http://content7.flixster.com/movie/11/17/62/11176245_mob.jpg\",\"profile\":\"http://content7.flixster.com/movie/11/17/62/11176245_pro.jpg\",\"detailed\":\"http://content7.flixster.com/movie/11/17/62/11176245_det.jpg\",\"original\":\"http://content7.flixster.com/movie/11/17/62/11176245_ori.jpg\"},\"abridged_cast\":[{\"name\":\"Paul Walker\",\"id\":\"162654234\",